<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Frances Lefkowitz</span></strong> is the author of two books, <em>Marilyn Monroe</em> and <em>David Letterman</em>, both part of Chelsea House Publishers&rsquo; acclaimed Pop Culture Legends series. Her memoir in this issue is part of a book-in-progress about growing up poor, white, and female in the San Francisco of the 1960s and &rsquo;70s. She currently lives in coastal Maine and recently left her job as senior editor for <em>Body &amp; Soul</em> magazine to concentrate on writing her book and pursuing her hobbies, which include surfing and perfecting her Spanish.</p><a href="/contributors/frances-lefkowitz" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
