			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1999">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>In January 1980, I returned to college as a twenty-four-year-old single mother of a two-year-old boy. I learned all too quickly that my fellow students were likely to spend more on their cocaine habits than I received on welfare each month: $287, if my memory serves me right.</p>

<p>I was deeply moved by Frances Lefkowitz&rsquo;s memoir &ldquo;<a href="/article/587">The Gifted Classes</a>&rdquo; [January 2003]. For the gifted members of this country&rsquo;s underclass, the desire and opportunity to pursue our dreams doesn&rsquo;t come without a price. Lefkowitz charted the hairpin turns and emotional tailspins of that journey with eloquence and tragic beauty.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Nancy Flynn<br>Corvallis, Oregon</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

